The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Fresh Tata push to Bangla plan

 Dhaka, March 14 (PTI): 

 The Tata group has renewed its efforts to gauge the mind 

 of the caretaker government regarding its proposed $3 billion 

 investment in Bangladesh. 

 Tata group resident director Manzer Hossain met communications adviser M.A. Matin and discussed the latest developments related to the groups proposed investments in the country.

 We are yet to get any indication regarding resumption of talks on the investment proposals, Hossain said.

 The adviser suggested that Hossain discuss the issue with the relevant ministry. 

 The industries ministry is the authority to deal with such projects while the governments Board of Investment, the investment promotion agency, is the custodian of the review report on the Tatas investment proposal, Matin said. 




